EXPENSE & INCOME TRACKER (Python + SQLite)

Submitted by: Manak Agarwal
Roll No.: 25BAI10225
Course Project: Vityarthi Flipped Course Project
Acknowledgment

I would like to express my gratitude to everyone who supported me during the development of this project. Their guidance and encouragement helped me complete this project successfully

Abstract

Managing personal finance is an important skill in everyday life. This project, Expense & Income Tracker, is a Python-based console application that helps users record and review financial transactions easily. The system uses SQLite as a lightweight and persistent database to store the data locally. Users can track expenses, income, calculate total balance, and manage transaction history convenientl

Introduction

With increasing digitalization, simple tools for daily financial management have become essential. People need to monitor spending habits in order to save money and control unnecessary expenses.

This project provides:

A terminal-based interface

A local storage database

Real-time financial summary updates


The main focus is to create a minimal and effective system that is easy to operate.

Objective

To record expense and income data efficiently

To maintain a local secure financial record

To calculate total income, expenses, and balance automatically

To provide a simple and user-friendly interface

To allow removal of transaction history when neede

Software Requirements

Component	Description

Programming Language	Python 3
Database	SQLite3
IDE / Editor	Any (VS Code / PyCharm / IDLE)
Operating System	Windows / Linux / macOS

